# Modern Background Paths

Hero background with four cycling SVG path animation patterns — Neural (random network nodes and connections), Flow (organic bezier waves), Geometric (grid cell fill), and Spiral. Patterns auto-advance every 12 seconds. Text title uses letter-by-letter spring entrance via Framer Motion.

## Use when
- Building a dark or light landing page hero with a living, animated SVG background.
- Creating a first-load reveal where the background animates into view.
- Emphasizing a value proposition above the fold with an immersive visual layer.
- Showcasing a product with a dynamic, auto-cycling background pattern.

## Stack
- Framework: react
- Libraries: framer-motion, @radix-ui/react-slot, class-variance-authority
- Requires: tailwind, shadcn

## Install
```bash
framer-motion, @radix-ui/react-slot, class-variance-authority
```

## Component — modern-background-paths.tsx
```tsx
"use client"

import { motion } from "framer-motion"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { useState, useEffect } from "react"

function GeometricPaths() {
  const gridSize = 40
  const paths = []
  for (let x = 0; x < 20; x++) {
    for (let y = 0; y < 12; y++) {
      if (Math.random() > 0.7) {
        paths.push({
          id: `grid-${x}-${y}`,
          d: `M${x * gridSize},${y * gridSize} L${(x + 1) * gridSize},${y * gridSize} L${(x + 1) * gridSize},${(y + 1) * gridSize} L${x * gridSize},${(y + 1) * gridSize} Z`,
          delay: Math.random() * 5,
        })
      }
    }
  }
  return (
    <svg className="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full opacity-20" viewBox="0 0 800 480">
      {paths.map((path) => (
        <motion.path
          key={path.id}
          d={path.d}
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          strokeWidth="1"
          initial={{ pathLength: 0, opacity: 0 }}
          animate={{ pathLength: [0, 1, 0], opacity: [0, 0.6, 0], scale: [1, 1.05, 1] }}
          transition={{ duration: 8, delay: path.delay, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
        />
      ))}
    </svg>
  )
}

// [FlowPaths, NeuralPaths, SpiralPaths components — see source for full implementations]

export default function EnhancedBackgroundPaths({
  title = "Neural Dynamics",
}: {
  title?: string
}) {
  const [currentPattern, setCurrentPattern] = useState(0)
  const patterns = ['neural', 'flow', 'geometric', 'spiral']
  const words = title.split(" ")

  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(() => {
      setCurrentPattern((prev) => (prev + 1) % patterns.length)
    }, 12000)
    return () => clearInterval(interval)
  }, [])

  return (
    <div className="relative min-h-screen w-full flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 via-white to-slate-100 dark:from-slate-900 dark:via-slate-800 dark:to-slate-900">
      <div className="absolute inset-0 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
        <motion.div key={currentPattern} initial={{ opacity: 0 }} animate={{ opacity: 1 }} exit={{ opacity: 0 }} transition={{ duration: 2 }}>
          {/* renderPattern() based on currentPattern */}
        </motion.div>
      </div>
      {/* [Title letter animation, CTA button, pattern indicator — see source] */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Demo
```tsx
import BackgroundPaths from "@/components/ui/modern-background-paths";

const DemoOne = () => {
  return <BackgroundPaths />;
};

export { DemoOne };
```

## Notes
- The `GeometricPaths`, `FlowPaths`, `NeuralPaths`, and `SpiralPaths` sub-components use `Math.random()` at render time to generate paths — the SVG will look different on each render/hydration. For SSR consistency, seed the random values or use `useMemo`.
- `@radix-ui/react-slot` and `class-variance-authority` are indirect dependencies via the shadcn Button component used in the CTA.
